     <div type="encomium">
   <head>
      <hi>M.D.</hi> Esquire, To his good Friend, <hi>T.V.</hi>
   </head>
   <l>WHat Thou do'st teach, by others heretofore</l>
   <l>Hath likewise bin. But yet by no man <gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap>
   </l>
   <l>To the true life. That by thy godly care,</l>
   <l>Thou and thine Authour equally doe share.</l>
   <l>Thou praisest him Translating, but if he</l>
   <l>Vnderstood English he would more praise th<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="2 letters">
         <desc>••</desc>
      </gap>e.</l>
   <l>Thou to our Nation ha'st his Doctrine showne;</l>
   <l>Which to our vulgar else had not <gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>eene knowne;</l>
   <l>As much by this thou get'st as ere he wan<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="2 letters">
         <desc>••</desc>
      </gap>:</l>
   <l>
      <hi>England</hi> praise <hi>Vicars, D<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>nt<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>k</hi> her,<hi>Ke<gap reason="illegible" resp="#murp" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>ke<gap reason="illegible" resp="#murp" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>man.</hi>
   </l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Mich. Drayton</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
